.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH DELPHI-TIME 1  "delphitools-cli 0.1.0" "delphitools manual"
.SH NAME
time \- Unix timestamp and date arithmetic
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtime\fR [\fB\-\-to\fR] [\fB\-\-tz\fR] [\fB\-\-add\fR] [\fB\-\-sub\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIINPUT\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Unix timestamp and date arithmetic
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<TO>\fR
Output format(s): iso, rfc2822, rfc3339, unix, human. Default: all
.TP
\fB\-\-tz\fR \fI<TZ>\fR
Timezone (IANA name, e.g. America/New_York)
.TP
\fB\-\-add\fR \fI<ADD>\fR
Add a duration (e.g. 30d, 5h, 90m)
.TP
\fB\-\-sub\fR \fI<SUB>\fR
Subtract a duration
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIINPUT\fR]

